      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Current scientific consensus does not support the idea that there are significant, inherent biological differences in muscle fiber composition or overall athletic potential across different racial groups that would necessitate different training programming. Biological variability within any population is far greater than any purported average differences between racial groups. Programming should instead be tailored based on individual factors like genetics, training history, current fitness level, and specific goals. Focusing on these individual variables will yield much better results than grouping clients based on race.",
